Apple seeded the <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/2025/04/21/ios-18-5-beta-3-developers/">third beta of iOS 18.5</a> to developers today, and so far the software update includes only a few minor changes.<br/>
<br/>
<img src="https://images.macrumors.com/article-new/2025/04/iOS-18.5-Apple-Intelligence-Color-Palette-Feature.jpg" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-999304" /><br/>
The changes are in the Mail and Settings apps.<br/>
<br/>
In the Mail app, you can now easily turn off contact photos directly within the app, by tapping on the circle with three dots in the top-right corner.<br/>
<br/>
<img src="https://images.macrumors.com/article-new/2025/04/mail-categories-ios-18-5.jpg" alt="" width="2000" height="1125" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-997478" /><br/>
In the Settings app, AppleCare+ coverage information is more prominent.<br/>
<br/>
<img src="https://images.macrumors.com/article-new/2025/04/applecare-logo-ios-18-5.jpg" alt="" width="2000" height="1125" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-997479" /><br/>
